ce|last=Peterson|first=Rick|date=20 March 2020|website=Rick Peterson: Conservative Leader 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\nWithdrew due to tight election timeline and rules. Peterson also cited the ongoing [[COVID-19 pandemic in Canada|COVID-19 pandemic crisis]] as his stated reason for suspending his campaign.<ref name=\":7\" />\n:'''Date registered with Elections Canada:'''\n:'''Campaign website:''' {{URL|rickcpc.ca}}\n;Policies: \n*Implement a 15% federal [[flat tax]]<ref name=\"petersonnp\">{{cite news |title=Rick Peterson looks to shake up the Conservative leadership race with flat tax plan |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/rick-peterson-looks-to-shake-up-the-conservative-leadership-race-with-flat-tax-plan |accessdate=29 January 2020 |work=National Post |date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n*Eliminate the federal corporate income tax\n*Repeal of [[Bill C-48]]<ref name=\"petersonnp\" />\n*Replace the federal [[carbon tax]] with a levy on heavy emitters<ref name=\"petersonnp\" />\n*End supply management\n{{Endorsements box\n|df=yes| title = Endorsements of Rick Peterson\n| list =\n;'''MPs:'''\n;'''Senators:'''\n*[[Stephen Greene (politician)|Stephen Greene]] (Senator for [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]]-[[Citadel Hill (Fort George)|The Citadel]], [[Nova Scotia]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/RickCPC/posts/2974751252569301:0|title=I'm honoured and grateful to have Senator Stephen Greene supporting my leadership campaign. Thank you, Senator!|first=Rick|last=Peterson|date=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n;'''Provincial politicians:'''\n;'''Municipal politicians:'''\n;'''Former MPs:'''\n;'''Former Senators:'''\n;'''Former provincial politicians:'''\n*[[Lorne Mayencourt]] (Peterson's campaign manager; BC MLA for [[Vancouver-Burrard]] 2001-2008)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RPSuitsandBoots/status/1220865760119013376?s=20|title=Stoked to have this man running our @CPC_HQ leadership drive.|first=Rick|l