carbon_tax |website=Derek Sloan for Leader|access-date = 19 April 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|Energy\n|\n*Repeal Bill C-69 (\"The modernization of the National Energy Board and Canadian Environmental Assessment Agency\") and C-48 (\"An Act respecting the regulation of vessels that transport crude oil or persistent oil\") to promote pipeline construction<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n|\n*Repeal Bill C-69 (\"The modernization of the National Energy Board and Canadian Environmental Assessment Agency\") and C-48 (\"An Act respecting the regulation of vessels that transport crude oil or persistent oil\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://petermackay.ca/en-CA/government-blockades-blocus-gouvernement|title=Stop the Government Blockades &#124; Peter MacKay|website=petermackay.ca}}</ref>\n|\n*\n|\n*Repeal Bill C-69 (\"The modernization of the National Energy Board and Canadian Environmental Assessment Agency\") and C-48 (\"An Act respecting the regulation of vessels that transport crude oil or persistent oil\") to promote pipeline construction<ref>{{cite web |title=Energy and Resource Development |url=https://www.dereksloan.ca/energy_and_resource_development |website=Derek Sloan for Leader|access-date = 19 April 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|Speech\n|\n*Protect free speech by opposing Bill C-16 (which adds gender expression and gender identity as protected grounds to the Canadian Human Rights Act) and C-8 (which bans [[conversion therapy]])<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n|\n*\n|\n*\n|\n*Protect free speech by opposing Bill C-16 (which adds gender expression and gender identity as protected grounds to the Canadian Human Rights Act)<ref>{{cite web |title=Free Speech in Canada |url=https://www.dereksloan.ca/free_speech_in_canada |website=Derek Sloan for Leader|access-date = 19 April 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|Firearms\n|\n*Review firearm laws and reduce bureaucracy<ref>{{cite web |title=I\u2019ve been listening to Party members who care deeply about this issue. Their message is clear: