usinesses or households<ref>{{cite news |title=Erin O\u2019Toole: This is how I would get our country working again {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/opinion/erin-otoole-this-is-how-i-would-make-this-country-work |date=26 February 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref>\n*Use [[Section 33 of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms|the notwithstanding clause]] to impose mandatory minimum sentences for violent crime<ref>{{cite news |title=Jason Kenney endorses Erin O\u2019Toole for leadership of Conservative party {{!}} National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/canada-news-pmn/otoole-mackay-set-to-kick-conservative-leadership-campaigns-up-a-notch |date=5 March 2020 |language=en-CA}}</ref>\n|\n*Revoke the citizenship of dual citizens who are convicted terrorists<ref>{{cite web |title=A Safe Canada\u2014Fighting Terrorism |url=https://www.dereksloan.ca/fighting_terrorism |website=Derek Sloan for Leader|access-date = 19 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Raise the minimum age required to purchase cannabis to 25<ref>{{cite web |title=Marijuana |url=https://www.dereksloan.ca/marijuana |website=Derek Sloan for Leader|access-date = 19 April 2020}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|Abortion\n|\n*Ban sex-selective abortions<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n*Free votes for MPs on conscience issues<ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n|\n*MacKay is pro-choice and supports [[same-sex marriage]].  Following the 2019 federal election, he was critical of Andrew Scheer's handing of the issues of abortion and same-sex marriage, saying that the issues had held the party back.<ref>{{cite news |last1=The Canadian Press |title=Peter MacKay regrets how 'stinking albatross' comments were viewed |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatchewan/peter-mackay-regina-visit-1.5489675 |accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=[[CBC News]] |date=6 March 2020|author1-link=The Canadian Press }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Taylor |first1=Stephanie |title=Peter MacKay regrets how his 'stinking albatross' comment after federal electio